name: tofu & veggies in peanut sauce
instructions:
1. Heat oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat. 

2. Cut broccoli, red bell pepper, mushrooms and tofu into bite-sized pieces.

3. Add to hot oil and stir-fry for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.

4. In a small bowl combine peanut butter, hot water, vinegar, molasses and soy sauce.

5. Add sauce to pan and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes, or until vegetables are tender crisp.
